  description: "asyncio.Future additional method __qualname__ checks in asynciotaskqn124 namespace — wave 255 theme: Future.set_result.__qualname__.__eq__('Future.set_result')==True (len=17: 'Future.'=7+'set_result'=10); Future.set_result.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor')==True (C-level method); Future.set_exception.__qualname__.__eq__('Future.set_exception')==True (len=20: 'Future.'=7+'set_exception'=13); Future.set_exception.__qualname__.__len__()==20; Future.exception.__qualname__.__eq__('Future.exception')==True (len=16: 'Future.'=7+'exception'=9); Future.exception.__qualname__.__len__()==16; Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__.__eq__('Future.add_done_callback')==True (len=24: 'Future.'=7+'add_done_callback'=17, longest Future method qualname and two more than Task.add_done_callback len=22 because 'Future.'=7 vs 'Task.'=5); Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__.__len__()==24; all Future methods are C-level method_descriptors; set_result and set_exception are the two state-mutation methods for a Future; add_done_callback registers a callback called when Future transitions to done state; verified with Python 3.14.3"
