  description: "asyncio Task and Future method class name and qualname length comparison in asynciotaskqn124 namespace — wave 255 theme: Task.get_name.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor')==True (Task-specific name-management method, C-level); Task.set_name.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor')==True; Task.get_coro.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor')==True (Task.get_coro returns the wrapped coroutine); qualname length comparison: Task.result=11 < Task.get_name=13 = Task.set_name=13 = Task.get_coro=13 < Task.add_done_callback=22; Future.exception=16 < Future.set_result=17 < Future.set_exception=20 < Future.add_done_callback=24; Task.add_done_callback len=22 vs Future.add_done_callback len=24 (difference of 2 = len('Future')-len('Task')=6-4=2); Future.add_done_callback at len=24 is the longest method qualname in this spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"
